Column Comment.0: INFORMATION ITEM SUBTYPE: the type of information item. May be one of Thevalid types of Information item as defined by check constraints.
Column Comment.1: INFORMATION ITEM ID: Unique identifier for the information item.
Column Comment.2: QUALITYE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the record describing a qualitycharacteristic of the information item.
Column Comment.3: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.4: COMPLETENESS DESCRIPTION: A narrative description of the completeness ofthis information item. Information aobut omissons, selction criteria, generlaization,definitions used and other rules used to generate this dataset.
Column Comment.5: COORDINATE ACCURACY DESCRIPTION: An assessement of the accuracy of thespatial objects, including horizontal accuracy and vertical accuracy.
Column Comment.6: COORD ACQUISITION: identifies an assembly of coordinate data that must begrouped together. It should be acquired together at the same time, from the samesource, using the same method and at the same accuracy. May be used to indicatethe level of accuracy of a set of coordinates.
Column Comment.7: COORDINATE QUALITY: the quality of the coordiante, such as validated,unvalidated, poor etc. for any spatial or positional information contained on theinformation item.
Column Comment.8: COORDINATE QUALITY DESCRIPTION: Narrative descriptive comments about thequality of the coordinate or spatial data in the information item.
Column Comment.9: MAINTENANCE DUE DATE: the date when the next maintenance event is due.
Column Comment.10: DEFICIENCY INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that this quality measure has adeficiency associated with it.
Column Comment.11: DEFICIENCY TYPE: The type of deficiency that has been found.
Column Comment.12: DESCRIBED BY BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: Validated business associate id for theBUSINESS ASSOCIATE who conducted or was responsible for identifying thisquality measure.
Column Comment.13: DESCRIPTION: A narrative description of the quality of the information item.
Column Comment.14: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.15: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.16: HORIZONTAL ACCURACY: A measure of the accuracy of a horizontal locationrelative to its true position.
Column Comment.17: HORIZONTAL ACCURACY DESCRIPTION: A short narrative description about theaccuracy of the horizontal locations.
Column Comment.19: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.20: QUALITY DATE: the date that this quality measure was recorded. For the range ofdates that this quality was in effect, please use effective and expiry dates.
Column Comment.21: REMARK: Narrative remarks relating to this row of data.
Column Comment.22: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.23: VERTICAL ACCURACY: A measure of the accuracy of a vertical location relative toits true position.
Column Comment.24: VERTICAL ACCURACY DESCRIPTION: A short narrative description about theaccuracy of the vertical locations.
Column Comment.26: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.27: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.28: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.29: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.30: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.31: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.32: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
